The Czech stock index increased for
a second day as gains at power utility  CEZ AS (CEZ)  and  Komercni Banka
AS (KOMB)  outweighed declines at Telefonica Czech Republic AS.  The PX gauge of companies added 0.7 percent to 994.3 as of
10:14 a.m. in  Prague , paring this weekâ€™s declines to 9 percent.
CEZ, which has a 20 percent weighting in the index, jumped 2.1
percent to 766 koruna. Komercni Banka added 2 percent to 3,059
koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
